revisions.description: Added following OBJECT-GROUP: - ctspNotifCtrlGroup - ctspNotifGroup - ctspNotifInfoGroup - ctspIfSgtMappingGroup - ctspVlanSgtMappingGroup - ctspSgtCachingGroup - ctspSgaclMonitorGroup - ctspSgaclMonitorStatisticGroup Added new compliance - ciscoTrustSecPolicyMIBCompliances Modified ctspIpSgtSource to add l3if(6), vlan(7), caching(8).
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoTrustSecPolicyMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-lan-switch-snmp@cisco.com
ciscoTrustSecPolicyMIB.description: This MIB module defines managed objects that facilitate the management of various policies within the Cisco Trusted Security (TrustSec) infrastructure. The information available through this MIB includes: o Device and interface level configuration for enabling SGACL (Security Group Access Control List) enforcement on Layer2/3 traffic. o Administrative and operational SGACL mapping to Security Group Tag (SGT). o Various statistics counters for traffic subject to SGACL enforcement. o TrustSec policies with respect to peer device. o Interface level configuration for enabling the propagation of SGT along with the Layer 3 traffic in portions of network which does not have the capability to support TrustSec feature. o TrustSec policies with respect to SGT propagation with Layer 3 traffic. The following terms are used throughout this MIB: VRF: Virtual Routing and Forwarding. SGACL: Security Group Access Control List. ACE: Access Control Entries. SXP: SGT Propagation Protocol. SVI: Switch Virtual Interface. IPM: Identity Port Mapping. SGT (Security Group Tag) is a unique 16 bits value assigned to every security group and used by network devices to enforce SGACL. Peer is another device connected to the local device on the other side of a TrustSec link. Default Policy: Policy applied to traffic when there is no explicit policy between the SGT associated with the originator of the traffic and the SGT associated with the destination of the traffic.

ctspSgaclEnforcementEnable.name: ctspSgaclEnforcementEnable
ctspSgaclEnforcementEnable.description: This object specifies whether SGACL enforcement for all Layer 3 interfaces (excluding SVIs) is enabled at the managed system. 'none' indicates that SGACL enforcement for all Layer 3 interfaces (excluding SVIs) is disabled. 'l3Only' indicates that SGACL enforcement is enabled on every TrustSec capable Layer3 interface (excluding SVIs) in the device.

ctspSgaclIpv4DropNetflowMonitor.name: ctspSgaclIpv4DropNetflowMonitor
ctspSgaclIpv4DropNetflowMonitor.description: This object specifies an existing flexible netflow monitor name used to collect and export the IPv4 traffic dropped packets statistics due to SGACL enforcement. The zero-length string indicates that no such netflow monitor is configured in the device.

ctspSgaclIpv6DropNetflowMonitor.name: ctspSgaclIpv6DropNetflowMonitor
ctspSgaclIpv6DropNetflowMonitor.description: This object specifies an existing flexible netflow monitor name used to collect and export the IPv6 traffic dropped packets statistics due to SGACL enforcement. The zero-length string indicates that no such netflow monitor is configured in the device.

ctspVlanConfigTable.name: ctspVlanConfigTable
ctspVlanConfigTable.description: This table lists the SGACL enforcement for Layer 2 and Layer 3 switched packet in a VLAN as well as VRF information for VLANs in the device.

ctspVlanConfigEntry.name: ctspVlanConfigEntry
ctspVlanConfigEntry.description: Each row contains the SGACL enforcement information for Layer 2 and Layer 3 switched packets in a VLAN identified by its VlanIndex value. Entry in this table is populated for VLANs which contains SGACL enforcement or VRF configuration.

ctspVlanConfigIndex.name: ctspVlanConfigIndex
ctspVlanConfigIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN-ID of this VLAN.

ctspVlanConfigSgaclEnforcement.name: ctspVlanConfigSgaclEnforcement
ctspVlanConfigSgaclEnforcement.description: This object specifies the configured SGACL enforcement status for this VLAN i.e., 'true' = enabled and 'false' = disabled.

ctspVlanSviActive.name: ctspVlanSviActive
ctspVlanSviActive.description: This object indicates if there is an active SVI associated with this VLAN. 'true' indicates that there is an active SVI associated with this VLAN. and SGACL is enforced for both Layer 2 and Layer 3 switched packets within that VLAN. 'false' indicates that there is no active SVI associated with this VLAN, and SGACL is only enforced for Layer 2 switched packets within that VLAN.

ctspVlanConfigVrfName.name: ctspVlanConfigVrfName
ctspVlanConfigVrfName.description: This object specifies an existing VRF where this VLAN belongs to. The zero length value indicates this VLAN belongs to the default VRF.

ctspVlanConfigStorageType.name: ctspVlanConfigStorageType
ctspVlanConfigStorageType.description: The objects specifies the storage type for this conceptual row.

ctspVlanConfigRowStatus.name: ctspVlanConfigRowStatus
ctspVlanConfigRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row entry. This object is used to manage creation and deletion of rows in this table. When this object value is 'active', other writable objects in the same row cannot be modified.

ctspConfigSgaclMappingTable.name: ctspConfigSgaclMappingTable
ctspConfigSgaclMappingTable.description: This table contains the SGACLs information which is applied to unicast IP traffic which carries a source SGT and travels to a destination SGT.

ctspConfigSgaclMappingEntry.name: ctspConfigSgaclMappingEntry
ctspConfigSgaclMappingEntry.description: Each row contains the SGACL mapping to source and destination SGT for a certain traffic type as well as status of this instance. A row instance can be created or removed by setting the appropriate value of its RowStatus object.

ctspConfigSgaclMappingIpTrafficType.name: ctspConfigSgaclMappingIpTrafficType
ctspConfigSgaclMappingIpTrafficType.description: This object indicates the type of the unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT and travelling to destination SGT and subjected to SGACL enforcement.

ctspConfigSgaclMappingDestSgt.name: ctspConfigSgaclMappingDestSgt
ctspConfigSgaclMappingDestSgt.description: This object indicates the destination SGT value. Value of zero indicates that the destination SGT is unknown.

ctspConfigSgaclMappingSourceSgt.name: ctspConfigSgaclMappingSourceSgt
ctspConfigSgaclMappingSourceSgt.description: This object indicates the source SGT value. Value of zero indicates that the source SGT is unknown.

ctspConfigSgaclMappingSgaclName.name: ctspConfigSgaclMappingSgaclName
ctspConfigSgaclMappingSgaclName.description: This object specifies the list of existing SGACLs which is administratively configured to apply to unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT to the destination SGT.

ctspConfigSgaclMappingStorageType.name: ctspConfigSgaclMappingStorageType
ctspConfigSgaclMappingStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

ctspConfigSgaclMappingRowStatus.name: ctspConfigSgaclMappingRowStatus
ctspConfigSgaclMappingRowStatus.description: This object is used to manage the creation and deletion of rows in this table. ctspConfigSgaclName may be modified at any time.

ctspConfigSgaclMonitor.name: ctspConfigSgaclMonitor
ctspConfigSgaclMonitor.description: This object specifies whether SGACL monitor mode is turned on for the configured SGACL enforced traffic.

ctspDefConfigIpv4Sgacls.name: ctspDefConfigIpv4Sgacls
ctspDefConfigIpv4Sgacls.description: This object specifies the SGACLs of the unicast default policy for IPv4 traffic. If there is no SGACL configured for unicast default policy for IPv4 traffic, the value of this object is the zero-length string.

ctspDefConfigIpv6Sgacls.name: ctspDefConfigIpv6Sgacls
ctspDefConfigIpv6Sgacls.description: This object specifies the SGACLs of the unicast default policy for IPv6 traffic. If there is no SGACL configured for unicast default policy for IPv6 traffic, the value of this object is the zero-length string.

ctspDownloadedSgaclMappingTable.name: ctspDownloadedSgaclMappingTable
ctspDownloadedSgaclMappingTable.description: This table contains the downloaded SGACLs information applied to unicast IP traffic which carries a source SGT and travels to a destination SGT.

ctspDownloadedSgaclMappingEntry.name: ctspDownloadedSgaclMappingEntry
ctspDownloadedSgaclMappingEntry.description: Each row contains the downloaded SGACLs mapping. A row instance is added for each pair of <source SGT, destination SGT> which contains SGACL that is dynamically downloaded from ACS server.

ctspDownloadedSgaclDestSgt.name: ctspDownloadedSgaclDestSgt
ctspDownloadedSgaclDestSgt.description: This object indicates the destination SGT value. Value of zero indicates that the destination SGT is unknown.

ctspDownloadedSgaclSourceSgt.name: ctspDownloadedSgaclSourceSgt
ctspDownloadedSgaclSourceSgt.description: This object indicates the source SGT value. Value of zero indicates that the source SGT is unknown.

ctspDownloadedSgaclIndex.name: ctspDownloadedSgaclIndex
ctspDownloadedSgaclIndex.description: This object identifies the downloaded SGACL which is applied to unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT to the destination SGT.

ctspDownloadedSgaclName.name: ctspDownloadedSgaclName
ctspDownloadedSgaclName.description: This object indicates the name of downloaded SGACL which is applied to unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT to the destination SGT.

ctspDownloadedSgaclGenId.name: ctspDownloadedSgaclGenId
ctspDownloadedSgaclGenId.description: This object indicates the generation identification of downloaded SGACL which is applied to unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT to the destination SGT.

ctspDownloadedIpTrafficType.name: ctspDownloadedIpTrafficType
ctspDownloadedIpTrafficType.description: This object indicates the type of the unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT and travelling to destination SGT and subjected to SGACL enforcement by this downloaded default policy.

ctspDownloadedSgaclMonitor.name: ctspDownloadedSgaclMonitor
ctspDownloadedSgaclMonitor.description: This object indicates whether SGACL monitor mode is turned on for the downloaded SGACL enforced traffic.

ctspDefDownloadedSgaclMappingTable.name: ctspDefDownloadedSgaclMappingTable
ctspDefDownloadedSgaclMappingTable.description: This table contains the downloaded SGACLs information of the default policy applied to unicast IP traffic.

ctspDefDownloadedSgaclMappingEntry.name: ctspDefDownloadedSgaclMappingEntry
ctspDefDownloadedSgaclMappingEntry.description: Each row contains the downloaded SGACLs mapping. A row instance contains the SGACL information of the default policy dynamically downloaded from ACS server for unicast IP traffic.

ctspDefDownloadedSgaclIndex.name: ctspDefDownloadedSgaclIndex
ctspDefDownloadedSgaclIndex.description: This object identifies the SGACL of downloaded default policy applied to unicast IP traffic.

ctspDefDownloadedSgaclName.name: ctspDefDownloadedSgaclName
ctspDefDownloadedSgaclName.description: This object indicates the name of the SGACL of downloaded default policy applied to unicast IP traffic.

ctspDefDownloadedSgaclGenId.name: ctspDefDownloadedSgaclGenId
ctspDefDownloadedSgaclGenId.description: This object indicates the generation identification of the SGACL of downloaded default policy applied to unicast IP traffic.

ctspDefDownloadedIpTrafficType.name: ctspDefDownloadedIpTrafficType
ctspDefDownloadedIpTrafficType.description: This object indicates the type of the IP traffic subjected to SGACL enforcement by this downloaded default policy.

ctspDefDownloadedSgaclMonitor.name: ctspDefDownloadedSgaclMonitor
ctspDefDownloadedSgaclMonitor.description: This object indicates whether SGACL monitor mode is turned on for the default downloaded SGACL enforced traffic.

ctspOperSgaclMappingTable.name: ctspOperSgaclMappingTable
ctspOperSgaclMappingTable.description: This table contains the operational SGACLs information applied to unicast IP traffic which carries a source SGT and travels to a destination SGT.

ctspOperSgaclMappingEntry.name: ctspOperSgaclMappingEntry
ctspOperSgaclMappingEntry.description: Each row contains the operational SGACLs mapping. A row instance is added for each pair of <source SGT, destination SGT> which contains the SGACL that either statically configured at the device or dynamically downloaded from ACS server.

ctspOperIpTrafficType.name: ctspOperIpTrafficType
ctspOperIpTrafficType.description: This object indicates the type of the unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT and travelling to destination SGT and subjected to SGACL enforcement.

ctspOperSgaclDestSgt.name: ctspOperSgaclDestSgt
ctspOperSgaclDestSgt.description: This object indicates the destination SGT value. Value of zero indicates that the destination SGT is unknown.

ctspOperSgaclSourceSgt.name: ctspOperSgaclSourceSgt
ctspOperSgaclSourceSgt.description: This object indicates the source SGT value. Value of zero indicates that the source SGT is unknown.

ctspOperSgaclIndex.name: ctspOperSgaclIndex
ctspOperSgaclIndex.description: This object identifies the SGACL operationally applied to unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT to the destination SGT.

ctspOperationalSgaclName.name: ctspOperationalSgaclName
ctspOperationalSgaclName.description: This object indicates the name of the SGACL operationally applied to unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT to the destination SGT.

ctspOperationalSgaclGenId.name: ctspOperationalSgaclGenId
ctspOperationalSgaclGenId.description: This object indicates the generation identification of the SGACL operationally applied to unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT to the destination SGT.

ctspOperSgaclMappingSource.name: ctspOperSgaclMappingSource
ctspOperSgaclMappingSource.description: This object indicates the source of SGACL mapping for the SGACL operationally applied to unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT to the destination SGT. 'downloaded' indicates that the mapping is downloaded from ACS server. 'configured' indicates that the mapping is locally configured in the device.

ctspOperSgaclConfigSource.name: ctspOperSgaclConfigSource
ctspOperSgaclConfigSource.description: This object indicates the source of SGACL creation for this SGACL. 'configured' indicates that the SGACL is locally configured in the local device. 'downloaded' indicates that the SGACL is created at ACS server and downloaded to the local device.

ctspOperSgaclMonitor.name: ctspOperSgaclMonitor
ctspOperSgaclMonitor.description: This object indicates whether SGACL monitor mode is turned on for the SGACL enforced traffic.

ctspDefOperSgaclMappingTable.name: ctspDefOperSgaclMappingTable
ctspDefOperSgaclMappingTable.description: This table contains the operational SGACLs information of the default policy applied to unicast IP traffic.

ctspDefOperSgaclMappingEntry.name: ctspDefOperSgaclMappingEntry
ctspDefOperSgaclMappingEntry.description: A row instance contains the SGACL information of the default policy which is either statically configured at the device or dynamically downloaded from ACS server for unicast IP traffic.

ctspDefOperIpTrafficType.name: ctspDefOperIpTrafficType
ctspDefOperIpTrafficType.description: This object indicates the type of the unicast IP traffic subjected to default policy enforcement.

ctspDefOperSgaclIndex.name: ctspDefOperSgaclIndex
ctspDefOperSgaclIndex.description: This object identifies the SGACL of default policy operationally applied to unicast IP traffic.

ctspDefOperationalSgaclName.name: ctspDefOperationalSgaclName
ctspDefOperationalSgaclName.description: This object indicates the name of the SGACL of default policy operationally applied to unicast IP traffic.

ctspDefOperationalSgaclGenId.name: ctspDefOperationalSgaclGenId
ctspDefOperationalSgaclGenId.description: This object indicates the generation identification of the SGACL of default policy operationally applied to unicast IP traffic.

ctspDefOperSgaclMappingSource.name: ctspDefOperSgaclMappingSource
ctspDefOperSgaclMappingSource.description: This object indicates the source of SGACL mapping for the SGACL of default policy operationally applied to unicast IP traffic. 'downloaded' indicates that the mapping is downloaded from ACS server. 'configured' indicates that the mapping is locally configured in the device.

ctspDefOperSgaclConfigSource.name: ctspDefOperSgaclConfigSource
ctspDefOperSgaclConfigSource.description: This object indicates the source of SGACL creation for the SGACL of default policy operationally applied to unicast IP traffic. 'downloaded' indicates that the SGACL is created at ACS server and downloaded to the local device. 'configured' indicates that the SGACL is locally configured in the local device.

ctspDefOperSgaclMonitor.name: ctspDefOperSgaclMonitor
ctspDefOperSgaclMonitor.description: This object indicates whether SGACL monitor mode is turned on for the SGACL of default policy enforced traffic.

ctspDefConfigIpv4SgaclsMonitor.name: ctspDefConfigIpv4SgaclsMonitor
ctspDefConfigIpv4SgaclsMonitor.description: This object specifies whether SGACL monitor mode is turned on for the default configured SGACL enforced Ipv4 traffic.

ctspDefConfigIpv6SgaclsMonitor.name: ctspDefConfigIpv6SgaclsMonitor
ctspDefConfigIpv6SgaclsMonitor.description: This object specifies whether SGACL monitor mode is turned on for the default configured SGACL enforced Ipv6 traffic.

ctspSgaclMonitorEnable.name: ctspSgaclMonitorEnable
ctspSgaclMonitorEnable.description: This object specifies whether SGACL monitor mode is turned on for the entire system. It has precedence than the per SGACL ctspConfigSgaclMonitor control. It could act as safety mechanism to turn off monitor in case the monitor feature impact system performance.

ctspSgtStatsTable.name: ctspSgtStatsTable
ctspSgtStatsTable.description: This table describes SGACL statistics counters per a pair of <source SGT, destination SGT> that is capable of providing this information.

ctspSgtStatsEntry.name: ctspSgtStatsEntry
ctspSgtStatsEntry.description: Each row contains the SGACL statistics related to IPv4 or IPv6 packets carrying the source SGT travelling to the destination SGT and subjected to SGACL enforcement.

ctspStatsIpTrafficType.name: ctspStatsIpTrafficType
ctspStatsIpTrafficType.description: This object indicates the type of the unicast IP traffic carrying the source SGT and travelling to destination SGT and subjected to SGACL enforcement.

ctspStatsDestSgt.name: ctspStatsDestSgt
ctspStatsDestSgt.description: This object indicates the destination SGT value. Value of zero indicates that the destination SGT is unknown.

ctspStatsSourceSgt.name: ctspStatsSourceSgt
ctspStatsSourceSgt.description: This object indicates the source SGT value. Value of zero indicates that the source SGT is unknown.

ctspStatsIpSwDropPkts.name: ctspStatsIpSwDropPkts
ctspStatsIpSwDropPkts.description: This object indicates the number of software-forwarded IP packets which are dropped by SGACL.

ctspStatsIpHwDropPkts.name: ctspStatsIpHwDropPkts
ctspStatsIpHwDropPkts.description: This object indicates the number of hardware-forwarded IP packets which are dropped by SGACL.

ctspStatsIpSwPermitPkts.name: ctspStatsIpSwPermitPkts
ctspStatsIpSwPermitPkts.description: This object indicates the number of software-forwarded IP packets which are permitted by SGACL.

ctspStatsIpHwPermitPkts.name: ctspStatsIpHwPermitPkts
ctspStatsIpHwPermitPkts.description: This object indicates the number of hardware-forwarded IP packets which are permitted by SGACL.

ctspStatsIpSwMonitorPkts.name: ctspStatsIpSwMonitorPkts
ctspStatsIpSwMonitorPkts.description: This object indicates the number of software-forwarded IP packets which are SGACL enforced & monitored.

ctspStatsIpHwMonitorPkts.name: ctspStatsIpHwMonitorPkts
ctspStatsIpHwMonitorPkts.description: This object indicates the number of hardware-forwarded IP packets which are SGACL enforced & monitored.

ctspDefStatsTable.name: ctspDefStatsTable
ctspDefStatsTable.description: This table describes statistics counters for unicast IP traffic subjected to default unicast policy.

ctspDefStatsEntry.name: ctspDefStatsEntry
ctspDefStatsEntry.description: Each row contains the statistics counter for each IP traffic type.

ctspDefIpTrafficType.name: ctspDefIpTrafficType
ctspDefIpTrafficType.description: This object indicates the type of the IP traffic subjected to default unicast policy enforcement.

ctspDefIpSwDropPkts.name: ctspDefIpSwDropPkts
ctspDefIpSwDropPkts.description: This object indicates the number of software-forwarded IP packets which are dropped by default unicast policy.

ctspDefIpHwDropPkts.name: ctspDefIpHwDropPkts
ctspDefIpHwDropPkts.description: This object indicates the number of hardware-forwarded IP packets which are dropped by default unicast policy.

ctspDefIpSwPermitPkts.name: ctspDefIpSwPermitPkts
ctspDefIpSwPermitPkts.description: This object indicates the number of software-forwarded IP packets which are permitted by default unicast policy.

ctspDefIpHwPermitPkts.name: ctspDefIpHwPermitPkts
ctspDefIpHwPermitPkts.description: This object indicates the number of hardware-forwarded IP packets which are permitted by default unicast policy.

ctspDefIpSwMonitorPkts.name: ctspDefIpSwMonitorPkts
ctspDefIpSwMonitorPkts.description: This object indicates the number of software-forwarded IP packets which are monitored by default unicast policy.

ctspDefIpHwMonitorPkts.name: ctspDefIpHwMonitorPkts
ctspDefIpHwMonitorPkts.description: This object indicates the number of hardware-forwarded IP packets which are monitored by default unicast policy.

ctspAllPeerPolicyAction.name: ctspAllPeerPolicyAction
ctspAllPeerPolicyAction.description: This object allows user to specify the action to be taken with respect to all peer policies in the device. When read, this object always returns the value 'none'. 'none' - No operation. 'refresh' - Refresh all peer policies in the device.

ctspPeerPolicyTable.name: ctspPeerPolicyTable
ctspPeerPolicyTable.description: This table lists the peer policy information for each peer device.

ctspPeerPolicyEntry.name: ctspPeerPolicyEntry
ctspPeerPolicyEntry.description: Each row contains the managed objects for peer policies for each peer device based on its name.

ctspPeerName.name: ctspPeerName
ctspPeerName.description: This object uniquely identifies a peer device.

ctspPeerSgt.name: ctspPeerSgt
ctspPeerSgt.description: This object indicates the SGT value of this peer device.

ctspPeerSgtGenId.name: ctspPeerSgtGenId
ctspPeerSgtGenId.description: This object indicates the generation identification of the SGT value assigned to this peer device.

ctspPeerTrustState.name: ctspPeerTrustState
ctspPeerTrustState.description: This object indicates the TrustSec trust state of this peer device. 'trusted' indicates that this is a trusted peer device. 'noTrust' indicates that this peer device is not trusted.

ctspPeerPolicyLifeTime.name: ctspPeerPolicyLifeTime
ctspPeerPolicyLifeTime.description: This object indicates the policy life time which provides the time interval during which the peer policy is valid.

ctspPeerPolicyLastUpdate.name: ctspPeerPolicyLastUpdate
ctspPeerPolicyLastUpdate.description: This object indicates the time when this peer policy is last updated.

ctspPeerPolicyAction.name: ctspPeerPolicyAction
ctspPeerPolicyAction.description: This object allows user to specify the action to be taken with this peer policy. When read, this object always returns the value 'none'. 'none' - No operation. 'refresh' - Refresh this peer policy.

ctspLayer3PolicyTable.name: ctspLayer3PolicyTable
ctspLayer3PolicyTable.description: This table describes Layer 3 transport policy for IP traffic regarding SGT propagation.

ctspLayer3PolicyEntry.name: ctspLayer3PolicyEntry
ctspLayer3PolicyEntry.description: Each row contains the Layer 3 transport policies per IP traffic type per policy type.

ctspLayer3PolicyIpTrafficType.name: ctspLayer3PolicyIpTrafficType
ctspLayer3PolicyIpTrafficType.description: This object indicates the type of the IP traffic affected by Layer-3 transport policy. 'ipv4' indicates that the affected traffic is IPv4 traffic. 'ipv6' indicates that the affected traffic is IPv6 traffic.

ctspLayer3PolicyType.name: ctspLayer3PolicyType
ctspLayer3PolicyType.description: This object indicates the type of the Layer-3 transport policy affecting IP traffic regarding SGT propagation. 'permit' indicates that the transport policy is used to classify Layer-3 traffic which is subject to SGT propagation. 'exception' indicates that the transport policy is used to classify Layer-3 traffic which is NOT subject to SGT propagation.

ctspLayer3PolicyLocalConfig.name: ctspLayer3PolicyLocalConfig
ctspLayer3PolicyLocalConfig.description: This object specifies the name of an ACL that is administratively configured to classify Layer3 traffic. Zero-length string indicates there is no such configured policy.

ctspLayer3PolicyDownloaded.name: ctspLayer3PolicyDownloaded
ctspLayer3PolicyDownloaded.description: This object specifies the name of an ACL that is downloaded from policy server to classify Layer3 traffic. Zero-length string indicates there is no such downloaded policy.

ctspLayer3PolicyOperational.name: ctspLayer3PolicyOperational
ctspLayer3PolicyOperational.description: This object specifies the name of an operational ACL currently used to classify Layer3 traffic. Zero-length string indicates there is no such policy in effect.

ctspIfL3PolicyConfigTable.name: ctspIfL3PolicyConfigTable
ctspIfL3PolicyConfigTable.description: This table lists the interfaces which support Layer3 Transport policy.

ctspIfL3PolicyConfigEntry.name: ctspIfL3PolicyConfigEntry
ctspIfL3PolicyConfigEntry.description: Each row contains managed objects for Layer3 Transport on interface capable of providing this information.

ctspIfL3Ipv4PolicyEnabled.name: ctspIfL3Ipv4PolicyEnabled
ctspIfL3Ipv4PolicyEnabled.description: This object specifies whether the Layer3 Transport policies will be applied on this interface for egress IPv4 traffic. 'true' indicates that Layer3 permit and exception policy will be applied at this interface for egress IPv4 traffic. 'false' indicates that Layer3 permit and exception policy will not be applied at this interface for egress IPv4 traffic.

ctspIfL3Ipv6PolicyEnabled.name: ctspIfL3Ipv6PolicyEnabled
ctspIfL3Ipv6PolicyEnabled.description: This object specifies whether the Layer3 Transport policies will be applied on this interface for egress IPv6 traffic. 'true' indicates that Layer3 permit and exception policy will be applied at this interface for egress IPv6 traffic. 'false' indicates that Layer3 permit and exception policy will not be applied at this interface for egress IPv6 traffic.

ctspIpSgtMappingTable.name: ctspIpSgtMappingTable
ctspIpSgtMappingTable.description: This table contains the IP-to-SGT mapping information in the device.

ctspIpSgtMappingEntry.name: ctspIpSgtMappingEntry
ctspIpSgtMappingEntry.description: Each row contains the IP-to-SGT mapping and status of this instance. Entry in this table is either populated automatically by the device or manually configured by a user. A manually configured row instance can be created or removed by setting the appropriate value of its RowStatus object.

ctspIpSgtVrfName.name: ctspIpSgtVrfName
ctspIpSgtVrfName.description: This object indicates the VRF where IP-SGT mapping belongs to. The zero length value indicates the default VRF.

ctspIpSgtAddressType.name: ctspIpSgtAddressType
ctspIpSgtAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of Internet address.

ctspIpSgtIpAddress.name: ctspIpSgtIpAddress
ctspIpSgtIpAddress.description: This object indicates an Internet address. The type of this address is determined by the value of ctspIpSgtAddressType object.

ctspIpSgtAddressLength.name: ctspIpSgtAddressLength
ctspIpSgtAddressLength.description: This object indicates the length of an Internet address prefix.

ctspIpSgtValue.name: ctspIpSgtValue
ctspIpSgtValue.description: This object specifies the SGT value assigned to an Internet address.

ctspIpSgtSource.name: ctspIpSgtSource
ctspIpSgtSource.description: This object indicates the source of the mapping. 'configured' indicates that the mapping is manually configured by user. 'arp' indicates that the mapping is dynamically learnt from tagged ARP replies. 'localAuthenticated' indicates that the mapping is dynamically learnt from the device authentication of a host. 'sxp' indicates that the mapping is dynamically learnt from SXP (SGT Propagation Protocol). 'internal' indicates that the mapping is automatically created by the device between the device IP addresses and the device own SGT. 'l3if' indicates that Interface-SGT mapping is configured by user. 'vlan' indicates that Vlan-SGT mapping is configured by user. 'cached' indicates that sgt mapping is cached. Only 'configured' value is accepted when setting this object.

ctspIpSgtStorageType.name: ctspIpSgtStorageType
ctspIpSgtStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

ctspIpSgtRowStatus.name: ctspIpSgtRowStatus
ctspIpSgtRowStatus.description: This object is used to manage the creation and deletion of rows in this table. If this object value is 'active', user cannot modify any writable object in this row. If value of ctspIpSgtSource object in an entry is not 'configured', user cannot change the value of this object.

ctspAllSgtPolicyAction.name: ctspAllSgtPolicyAction
ctspAllSgtPolicyAction.description: This object allows user to specify the action to be taken with respect to all SGT policies in the device. When read, this object always returns the value 'none'. 'none' - No operation. 'refresh' - Refresh all SGT policies in the device.

ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyTable.name: ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyTable
ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyTable.description: This table lists the SGT policy information downloaded by the device.

ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyEntry.name: ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyEntry
ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyEntry.description: Each row contains the managed objects for SGT policies downloaded by the device.

ctspDownloadedSgtPolicySgt.name: ctspDownloadedSgtPolicySgt
ctspDownloadedSgtPolicySgt.description: This object indicates the SGT value for which the downloaded policy is applied to. Value of zero indicates that the SGT is unknown.

ctspDownloadedSgtPolicySgtGenId.name: ctspDownloadedSgtPolicySgtGenId

ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyLifeTime.name: ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyLifeTime
ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyLifeTime.description: This object indicates the policy life time which provides the time interval during which this downloaded policy is valid.

ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyLastUpdate.name: ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyLastUpdate
ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyLastUpdate.description: This object indicates the time when this downloaded SGT policy is last updated.

ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyAction.name: ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyAction
ctspDownloadedSgtPolicyAction.description: This object allows user to specify the action to be taken with this downloaded SGT policy. When read, this object always returns the value 'none'. 'none' - No operation. 'refresh' - Refresh this SGT policy.

ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicyTable.name: ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicyTable

ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicyEntry.name: ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicyEntry
ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicyEntry.description: Each row contains the managed objects for default SGT policies downloaded by the device.

ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicyType.name: ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicyType
ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicyType.description: This object indicates the downloaded default SGT policy type. 'unicastDefault' indicates the SGT policy applied to traffic which carries the default unicast SGT.

ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicySgtGenId.name: ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicySgtGenId
ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicySgtGenId.description: This object indicates the generation identification of the downloaded default SGT policy.

ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicyLifeTime.name: ctspDownloadedDefSgtPolicyLifeTime

ctspIfSgtValue.name: ctspIfSgtValue
ctspIfSgtValue.description: This object specifies the SGT value assigned to the interface.

ctspIfSgName.description: This object specifies the Security Group Name assigned to the interface.

ctspIfSgtStorageType.name: ctspIfSgtStorageType
ctspIfSgtStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

ctspL3IPMStatus.description: This object indicates the Layer 3 Identity Port Mapping(IPM) operational mode. disabled - The L3 IPM is not configured. active - The L3 IPM is configured for this interface, and SGT is available. inactive - The L3 IPM is configured for this interface, and SGT is unavailable.

ctspVlanSgtRowStatus.name: ctspVlanSgtRowStatus

ctspSgtCachingMode.name: ctspSgtCachingMode
ctspSgtCachingMode.description: This object specifies which SGT-caching mode is configured for SGT caching capable interfaces at the managed system. 'none' indicates that sgt-caching for all Layer 3 interfaces (excluding SVIs) is disabled. 'standAlone' indicates that SGT-caching is enabled on every TrustSec capable Layer3 interface (excluding SVIs) in the device. 'withEnforcement' indicates that SGT-caching is enabled on interfaces that have RBAC enforcement enabled. 'vlan' indicates that SGT-caching is enabled on the VLANs specified by ctspSgtCachingVlansfFirst2K & ctspSgtCachingVlansSecond2K

ctspSgtCachingVlansFirst2K.name: ctspSgtCachingVlansFirst2K
ctspSgtCachingVlansFirst2K.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANs 0 to 2047. If the bit corresponding to a VLAN is set to 1, it indicates SGT-caching is enabled on the VLAN. If the bit corresponding to a VLAN is set to 0, it indicates SGT-caching is disabled on the VLAN.

ctspSgtCachingVlansSecond2K.name: ctspSgtCachingVlansSecond2K
ctspSgtCachingVlansSecond2K.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANs 2048 to 4095. If the bit corresponding to a VLAN is set to 1, it indicates SGT-caching is enabled on the VLAN. If the bit corresponding to a VLAN is set to 0, it indicates SGT-caching is disabled on the VLAN.

ctspPeerPolicyUpdatedNotifEnable.name: ctspPeerPolicyUpdatedNotifEnable

ctspAuthorizationSgaclFailNotifEnable.name: ctspAuthorizationSgaclFailNotifEnable

ctspAuthorizationSgaclFailReason.name: ctspAuthorizationSgaclFailReason
ctspAuthorizationSgaclFailReason.description: This object indicates the reason of failure during SGACL acquisitions, installations and uninstallations, which is associated with ctspAuthorizationSgaclFailNotif; 'downloadACE' - Failure during downloading ACE in SGACL acquisition. 'downloadSrc' - Failure during downloading source list in SGACL acquisition. 'downloadDst' - Failure during downloading destination list in SGACL acquisition. 'installPolicy' - Failure during SGACL policy installation 'installPolicyStandby' - Failure during SGACL policy installation on standby 'installForIP' - Failure during SGACL installation for specific IP type. 'uninstall' - Failure during SGACL uninstallation.
